1
00:00:12,389 --> 00:00:15,986
<i>Episode 23</i>

2
00:00:18,122 --> 00:00:20,955
Hand over Jeong Gi Joon.

3
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:29,663
Then that would be the base
of trust you yourself create, no?

4
00:00:33,169 --> 00:00:37,613
And as the head of the
political faction called Milbon,

5
00:00:37,613 --> 00:00:39,756
inside the royal court,

6
00:00:39,756 --> 00:00:43,989
you could just insist on
a genuine parliament, no?

7
00:00:57,689 --> 00:01:00,972
You take the Haerye
and block the letters

8
00:01:00,972 --> 00:01:05,329
and I, afterward

9
00:01:05,329 --> 00:01:11,157
I'll spearhead Milbon and
realize Teacher Sambong's will.

10
00:01:18,387 --> 00:01:20,013
Is it power you want?

11
00:01:20,013 --> 00:01:22,381
If my desire

12
00:01:22,381 --> 00:01:24,857
to create the good nation

13
00:01:24,857 --> 00:01:28,990
of my thinking and of my
creed is greed for power,

14
00:01:28,990 --> 00:01:32,798
then greed for power it is.

15
00:01:32,798 --> 00:01:38,599
My identity as Milbon has been made known
to the King already, hence I can longer achieve
fame and prestige as a Confucian scholar.

16
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:43,204
However, I have no intention to
surrender as the King desires either.

17
00:01:43,204 --> 00:01:45,973
What do you want?

18
00:01:48,342 --> 00:01:52,720
Hand over the names of
all Milbon members to me.

19
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:56,761
And declare me as the new Bonwon

20
00:01:56,761 --> 00:02:00,190
and hand over the Milbon pledge to me.

21
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:04,502
Then you will give me Haerye?

22
00:02:04,502 --> 00:02:11,343
Though the King has yet to appoint the date,
he has already declared he will promulgate the letters.

23
00:02:11,343 --> 00:02:14,640
He would not promulgate
without the Haerye.

24
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:20,199
Hence, the Haerye is the best
weapon to block the promulgation.

25
00:02:20,199 --> 00:02:24,114
I will make it so that you can
have the Haerye at once, Bonwon.

26
00:02:24,114 --> 00:02:30,317
In everything, do as you will.

27
00:02:30,317 --> 00:02:37,396
Except, not as Milbon's Bonwon,
but personally, as Jeong Gi Joon.

28
00:02:41,436 --> 00:02:44,932
When do you want to hear my reply?

29
00:02:44,932 --> 00:02:47,287
There isn't time.

30
00:02:47,287 --> 00:02:51,572
I want the answer by
the day after tomorrow.

31
00:02:51,572 --> 00:02:55,957
I will be at the inn in Mapo.
Contact me.

32
00:02:55,957 --> 00:02:58,108
I will wait.

33
00:03:14,495 --> 00:03:18,774
Why did you select Lee Shin Jeok between
Lee Shin Jeok and Shim Jong Soo?

34
00:03:18,774 --> 00:03:19,533
Yes.

35
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:26,440
Minister Lee Shin Jeok is a veteran, so he doesn't
hold much influence over the young members.

36
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:32,032
Wouldn't Shim Jong Soo be
better suited to move Milbon?

37
00:03:34,181 --> 00:03:37,862
That's possible.

38
00:03:37,862 --> 00:03:43,224
However, Shim Jong Soo is lacking
in trickery, compared to Lee Shin Jeok.

39
00:03:43,224 --> 00:03:46,282
What trickery?

40
00:03:46,282 --> 00:03:48,829
Political influence, I mean.

41
00:03:48,829 --> 00:03:51,766
All the subjects in the current royal court,

42
00:03:51,766 --> 00:03:57,371
though they may each have
their fault, none are stupid.

43
00:03:57,371 --> 00:04:01,375
They are all people to be feared.

44
00:04:01,375 --> 00:04:04,540
Among them, to be able
to rise to the top three,

45
00:04:04,540 --> 00:04:10,299
means he stands atop
the vertex among the fierce.

46
00:04:11,819 --> 00:04:15,690
Though Lee Shin Jeok
is avaricious as a scholar,

47
00:04:15,690 --> 00:04:19,494
in the ability to draw people to his side,

48
00:04:19,494 --> 00:04:22,396
he is even greater than Minister Hwang Hee.

49
00:04:22,396 --> 00:04:29,014
He is someone who won't hesitate to use witchcraft
if he deems the circumstance ill. So of course.

50
00:04:29,014 --> 00:04:32,213
Why would you want to
appoint someone like him?

51
00:04:32,213 --> 00:04:35,576
